### Gateway flows — every request goes through :8080 (no direct service hits).
### IntelliJ's HTTP Client reads the `@name` annotation + `client.global.set(...)`
### bindings below; adjust or swap for your tool of choice.
###
### Prereqs:
###   docker compose up -d
###   Start config-service (8888), discovery-service (8761), user/product/order/gateway.
###   SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=local loads the seed data referenced below.

@gateway = http://localhost:8080
@ada     = 00000000-0000-7000-8000-000000000001
@product = 00000000-0000-7000-8000-00000000aa01


### 1. Login — gateway allowlists /api/v1/auth/**, so no token is needed here.
# @name login
POST {{gateway}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ada@example.com",
  "password": "Demo@1234"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("token", response.body.data.token);
%}


### 2. List products (JWT enforced by gateway).
GET {{gateway}}/api/v1/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 3. Place an order (JWT enforced; order-service publishes OrderCreatedV1 to RabbitMQ).
POST {{gateway}}/api/v1/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":    "{{ada}}",
  "productId": "{{product}}",
  "quantity":  1
}


### 4. List the caller's orders.
GET {{gateway}}/api/v1/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 5. Without a token → 401 from the gateway (enforcement filter).
GET {{gateway}}/api/v1/orders


### 6. Aggregated Swagger — pick a service from the top-right dropdown.
### UI:   http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html
### Spec: http://localhost:8080/v3/api-docs/user-service
GET {{gateway}}/v3/api-docs/user-service
